# Cloudflare and secrets: agent execution

1. **Vendor documentation first** (Cloudflare + xAI): before planning or implementing Cloudflare or xAI/Grok behavior, follow [docs/VENDOR_DOCUMENTATION_FIRST_CLOUDFLARE_XAI_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/VENDOR_DOCUMENTATION_FIRST_CLOUDFLARE_XAI_SSOT.md) and [.cursor/rules/vendor-documentation-first-cloudflare-xai.mdc](vendor-documentation-first-cloudflare-xai.mdc) — Cloudflare hub [developers.cloudflare.com/docs-for-agents/](https://developers.cloudflare.com/docs-for-agents/); xAI docs MCP **`https://docs.x.ai/api/mcp`** ([quickstart](https://docs.x.ai/developers/docs-mcp)).
2. **Read first**: `docs/AGENT_AUTOMATION_CLOUDFLARE_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md` (capability matrix, `op` field names, proactive checks); for Cursor MCP persistence (**§3.10** Environments **`cloudflare-mcp.env`** + **`envFile`**, verification) see `docs/CURSOR_CLOUDFLARE_MCP_AND_PLUGIN_SSOT.md`.
3. **Do not** tell the operator you cannot inspect **DNS** or **Cloudflare** state if **`user-cloudflare-api` MCP** `execute` is available: use it for **GET** inventory (zones, `dns_records`, workers) and cite the SSOT **zone id** for `centexmsp.net` from [TOKEN_ACCESS_STRATEGY_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/TOKEN_ACCESS_STRATEGY_SSOT.md).
4. **1Password**: use documented item **titles** and **fields** (e.g. API Credential → **`credential`**, not `password`). **Mint-once Cloudflare API tokens** → **`credential-manager` `store-cloudflare-token`** or **`op`** stdin wrappers — [CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_1PASSWORD_DEVELOPER_VAULT_2026-04-27.md) **Bootstrap / Pass 1**, [AGENT_AUTOMATION_CLOUDFLARE_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/AGENT_AUTOMATION_CLOUDFLARE_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md) **§2.2a**; see [CURSOR_CROSS_HOST_SYNC_PROTOCOL_2026-04-27.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_CROSS_HOST_SYNC_PROTOCOL_2026-04-27.md).
5. **Mutations / deploy**: `scripts/cloudflare-guard-preflight.sh` per [token-governance](token-governance-enforcement.mdc); portfolio tokens in [TOKEN_ACCESS_STRATEGY_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/TOKEN_ACCESS_STRATEGY_SSOT.md) before suggesting new API tokens.
6. **Maturity**: each session that touches Cloudflare, scan for **guard gaps**, **OIDC opportunities**, and **doc drift**; update the playbook in the same change set when process changes.
7. **Automation contract:** [NEW_CHAT_SINGLE_FILE_HANDOFF_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/NEW_CHAT_SINGLE_FILE_HANDOFF_SSOT.md) **§0** — operator **only** for **delegated `op`** (fingerprint) and **token mint**; deploy/guard use **Integrated Terminal** + **`lib-load-cf-deploy-token.sh`** / platform store / **`OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN`** before claiming the operator must run **wrangler**.
